#: ../../../topics/items.rst:5
msgid "Items"
msgstr "项目"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:10
msgid ""
"The main goal in scraping is to extract structured data from unstructured "
"sources, typically, web pages. :ref:`Spiders <topics-spiders>` may return "
"the extracted data as `items`, Python objects that define key-value pairs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:14
msgid ""
"Scrapy supports :ref:`multiple types of items <item-types>`. When you create "
"an item, you may use whichever type of item you want. When you write code "
"that receives an item, your code should :ref:`work for any item type "
"<supporting-item-types>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:22
msgid "Item Types"
msgstr "项目类型"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:24
msgid ""
"Scrapy supports the following types of items, via the `itemadapter`_ "
"library: :ref:`dictionaries <dict-items>`, :ref:`Item objects <item-"
"objects>`, :ref:`dataclass objects <dataclass-items>`, and :ref:`attrs "
"objects <attrs-items>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:33
msgid "Dictionaries"
msgstr "词典"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:35
msgid "As an item type, :class:`dict` is convenient and familiar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:40
msgid "Item objects"
msgstr "项目对象"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:42
msgid ""
":class:`Item` provides a :class:`dict`-like API plus additional features "
"that make it the most feature-complete item type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.item.Item:1
msgid "Base class for scraped items."
msgstr "用于支架物品的基础类"

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.item.Item:3
msgid ""
"In Scrapy, an object is considered an ``item`` if it's supported by the "
"`itemadapter`_ library. For example, when the output of a spider callback is "
"evaluated, only such objects are passed to :ref:`item pipelines <topics-item-"
"pipeline>`. :class:`Item` is one of the classes supported by `itemadapter`_ "
"by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.item.Item:9
msgid ""
"Items must declare :class:`Field` attributes, which are processed and stored "
"in the ``fields`` attribute. This restricts the set of allowed field names "
"and prevents typos, raising ``KeyError`` when referring to undefined fields. "
"Additionally, fields can be used to define metadata and control the way data "
"is processed internally. Please refer to the :ref:`documentation about "
"fields <topics-items-fields>` for additional information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.item.Item:16
msgid ""
"Unlike instances of :class:`dict`, instances of :class:`Item` may be :ref:"
"`tracked <topics-leaks-trackrefs>` to debug memory leaks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.item.Item.deepcopy:1
msgid "Return a :func:`~copy.deepcopy` of this item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.Item.fields:1
msgid ""
"A dictionary containing *all declared fields* for this Item, not only those "
"populated. The keys are the field names and the values are the :class:"
"`Field` objects used in the :ref:`Item declaration <topics-items-declaring>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:49
msgid ""
":class:`Item` objects replicate the standard :class:`dict` API, including "
"its ``__init__`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:52
msgid ":class:`Item` allows the defining of field names, so that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:54
msgid ""
":class:`KeyError` is raised when using undefined field names (i.e. prevents "
"typos going unnoticed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:57
msgid ""
":ref:`Item exporters <topics-exporters>` can export all fields by default "
"even if the first scraped object does not have values for all of them"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:61
msgid ""
":class:`Item` also allows the defining of field metadata, which can be used "
"to :ref:`customize serialization <topics-exporters-field-serialization>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:64
msgid ""
":mod:`trackref` tracks :class:`Item` objects to help find memory leaks (see :"
"ref:`topics-leaks-trackrefs`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:67 ../../../topics/items.rst:94
#: ../../../topics/items.rst:126 ../../../topics/items.rst:164
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "示例："

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:69
msgid ""
"from scrapy.item import Item, Field\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class CustomItem(Item):\n"
"    one_field = Field()\n"
"    another_field = Field()"
msgstr ""
"从 scrapy.item 导入项目，字段\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class CustomItem:\n"
"    one_field = Field()\n"
"    another_field = Field()"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:81
msgid "Dataclass objects"
msgstr "基准星对象"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:83
msgid ""
":func:`~dataclasses.dataclass` allows the defining of item classes with "
"field names, so that :ref:`item exporters <topics-exporters>` can export all "
"fields by default even if the first scraped object does not have values for "
"all of them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:87
msgid "Additionally, ``dataclass`` items also allow you to:"
msgstr "此外，``dataclass`` 项目也允许您："

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:89 ../../../topics/items.rst:119
msgid "define the type and default value of each defined field."
msgstr "定义每个定义字段的类型和默认值。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:91
msgid ""
"define custom field metadata through :func:`dataclasses.field`, which can be "
"used to :ref:`customize serialization <topics-exporters-field-"
"serialization>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:96
msgid ""
"from dataclasses import dataclass\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@dataclass\n"
"class CustomItem:\n"
"    one_field: str\n"
"    another_field: int"
msgstr ""
"从 dataclasses 导入 dataclass\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@dataclass\n"
"customitem:\n"
"    one_field: str\n"
"    another_field: int"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:106
msgid "Field types are not enforced at run time."
msgstr "字段类型在运行时没有强制执行。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:111
msgid "attr.s objects"
msgstr "对象"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:113
msgid ""
":func:`attr.s` allows the defining of item classes with field names, so "
"that :ref:`item exporters <topics-exporters>` can export all fields by "
"default even if the first scraped object does not have values for all of "
"them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:117
msgid "Additionally, ``attr.s`` items also allow to:"
msgstr "此外，``tot.s`` 项目也允许："

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:121
msgid ""
"define custom field :ref:`metadata <attrs:metadata>`, which can be used to :"
"ref:`customize serialization <topics-exporters-field-serialization>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:124
msgid ""
"In order to use this type, the :doc:`attrs package <attrs:index>` needs to "
"be installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:128
msgid ""
"import attr\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@attr.s\n"
"class CustomItem:\n"
"    one_field = attr.ib()\n"
"    another_field = attr.ib()"
msgstr ""
"导入 attr\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@tot.s\n"
"CustomItem:\n"
"    one_field = tot.ib()\n"
"    another_field = tot.ib()"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:142
msgid "Pydantic models"
msgstr "Pydantic模型"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:144
msgid ""
"`Pydantic <https://docs.pydantic.dev/>`_ models allow the defining of item "
"classes with field names, so that :ref:`item exporters <topics-exporters>` "
"can export all fields by default even if the first scraped object does not "
"have values for all of them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:149
msgid "Additionally, ``pydantic`` items also allow you to:"
msgstr "此外，``pydantic`` 项目也允许您："

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:151
msgid ""
"define the type and default value of each defined field with run-time type "
"validation."
msgstr "定义每个定义字段的类型和默认值，并进行运行时类型验证。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:154
msgid ""
"define custom field metadata through `pydantic.Field <https://docs.pydantic."
"dev/latest/concepts/fields/>`_, which can be used to :ref:`customize "
"serialization <topics-exporters-field-serialization>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:158
msgid ""
"benefit from automatic data validation and conversion based on type "
"annotations."
msgstr "基于类型注释的自动数据验证和转换的益处。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:161
msgid ""
"In order to use this type, the `pydantic package <https://docs.pydantic.dev/"
">`_ needs to be installed."
msgstr "为了使用此类型，需要安装 \"pydantic包 <https://docs.pydantic.dev/>\"。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:166
msgid ""
"from pydantic import BaseModel, Field\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class CustomItem(BaseModel):\n"
"    one_field: str = Field(default=\"\", description=\"First field\")\n"
"    another_field: int = Field(default=0, description=\"Second field\")"
msgstr ""
"从 pydantital 导入 BaseModel, 字段\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class CustomItem(BaseModel):\n"
"    one_field: str = Field(default=\"\", description=\"First field\")\n"
"    another_field: int = Field(default=0, description=\"第二个字段\")"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:175
msgid ""
"Unlike other item types, Pydantic models enforce field types at run time and "
"will raise validation errors for invalid data types."
msgstr ""
"与其他项目类型不同，Pydantic模型在运行时强制执行字段类型，并会引起无效数据类"
"型的验证错误。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:179 ../../../topics/items.rst:250
msgid "Working with Item objects"
msgstr "使用项目对象"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:184
msgid "Declaring Item subclasses"
msgstr "声明项子类"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:186
msgid ""
"Item subclasses are declared using a simple class definition syntax and :"
"class:`Field` objects. Here is an example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:189
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class Product(scrapy.Item):\n"
"    name = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    price = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    stock = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    tags = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    last_updated = scrapy.Field(serializer=str)"
msgstr ""
"导入 scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class Product(scrapy.Item):\n"
"    name = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    price = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    stock = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    tags = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    last_updated = scrapy.Field(serializer=str)"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:201
msgid ""
"Those familiar with `Django`_ will notice that Scrapy Items are declared "
"similar to `Django Models`_, except that Scrapy Items are much simpler as "
"there is no concept of different field types."
msgstr ""
"熟悉`Django`_ 的人会注意到报废物品类似于`Django Models`_, 除了废料条目更简"
"单，因为没有不同字段类型的概念。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:212
msgid "Declaring fields"
msgstr "声明字段"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:214
msgid ""
":class:`Field` objects are used to specify metadata for each field. For "
"example, the serializer function for the ``last_updated`` field illustrated "
"in the example above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:218
msgid ""
"You can specify any kind of metadata for each field. There is no restriction "
"on the values accepted by :class:`Field` objects. For this same reason, "
"there is no reference list of all available metadata keys. Each key defined "
"in :class:`Field` objects could be used by a different component, and only "
"those components know about it. You can also define and use any other :class:"
"`Field` key in your project too, for your own needs. The main goal of :class:"
"`Field` objects is to provide a way to define all field metadata in one "
"place. Typically, those components whose behaviour depends on each field use "
"certain field keys to configure that behaviour. You must refer to their "
"documentation to see which metadata keys are used by each component."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:229
msgid ""
"It's important to note that the :class:`Field` objects used to declare the "
"item do not stay assigned as class attributes. Instead, they can be accessed "
"through the :attr:`~scrapy.Item.fields` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.item.Field:1
msgid "Container of field metadata"
msgstr "字段元数据容器"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:235
msgid ""
"The :class:`Field` class is just an alias to the built-in :class:`dict` "
"class and doesn't provide any extra functionality or attributes. In other "
"words, :class:`Field` objects are plain-old Python dicts. A separate class "
"is used to support the :ref:`item declaration syntax <topics-items-"
"declaring>` based on class attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:241
msgid ""
"Field metadata can also be declared for ``dataclass`` and ``attrs`` items. "
"Please refer to the documentation for `dataclasses.field`_ and `attr.ib`_ "
"for additional information."
msgstr ""
"还可以对 ``dataclass`` 和 ``tours`` 两个项目声明字段元数据。请参考文档中的 "
"`dataclasses.field`_ 和 `tot.ib`_ 获取更多信息。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:254
msgid ""
"Here are some examples of common tasks performed with items, using the "
"``Product`` item :ref:`declared above  <topics-items-declaring>`. You will "
"notice the API is very similar to the :class:`dict` API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:259
msgid "Creating items"
msgstr "创建项目"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:261
msgid ""
">>> product = Product(name=\"Desktop PC\", price=1000)\n"
">>> print(product)\n"
"Product(name='Desktop PC', price=1000)"
msgstr ""
">>>> product = Product(name=\"Desktop PC\", price=1000)\n"
">>>> print(product)\n"
"Product(name='Desktop PC', price=1000)"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:269
msgid "Getting field values"
msgstr "获取字段值"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:271
msgid ""
">>> product[\"name\"]\n"
"Desktop PC\n"
">>> product.get(\"name\")\n"
"Desktop PC\n"
"\n"
">>> product[\"price\"]\n"
"1000\n"
"\n"
">>> product[\"last_updated\"]\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"    ...\n"
"KeyError: 'last_updated'\n"
"\n"
">>> product.get(\"last_updated\", \"not set\")\n"
"not set\n"
"\n"
">>> product[\"lala\"]  # getting unknown field\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"    ...\n"
"KeyError: 'lala'\n"
"\n"
">>> product.get(\"lala\", \"unknown field\")\n"
"'unknown field'\n"
"\n"
">>> \"name\" in product  # is name field populated?\n"
"True\n"
"\n"
">>> \"last_updated\" in product  # is last_updated populated?\n"
"False\n"
"\n"
">>> \"last_updated\" in product.fields  # is last_updated a declared field?\n"
"True\n"
"\n"
">>> \"lala\" in product.fields  # is lala a declared field?\n"
"False"
msgstr ""
">>>> product[\"name\"]\n"
"桌面PCformat@@1 >>> 产品 et(\"name\")\n"
"桌面PC\n"
"\n"
">> > product[\"price\"]\n"
"1000\n"
"\n"
">> > product[\"last_updated\"]\n"
"Traceby (最近一次来电):\n"
"    . .\n"
"密钥错误：“last _updated”\n"
"\n"
">> 产品 et(\"最后更新\", \"未设置\")\n"
"未设置\n"
"\n"
">>> product[\"lala\"] # 获取未知字段\n"
"Traceby (最近的通话时间):\n"
"    。 。\n"
"Key错误：'lala'\n"
"\n"
">> 产品 et(\"lala\", \"未知字段\")\n"
"\"未知字段\"\n"
"\n"
">>> 产品#中的“name”字段被填入？\n"
"True\n"
"\n"
">>> \"last _updated\" in product # is last_updated?\n"
"False\n"
"\n"
">> > > \"last _updated\" in product ields # 是最后更新一个声明的字段吗？\n"
"True\n"
"\n"
">>> \"lala\" 在产品中。fields # 是一个声明的字段吗？\n"
"False"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:311
msgid "Setting field values"
msgstr "设置字段值"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:313
msgid ""
">>> product[\"last_updated\"] = \"today\"\n"
">>> product[\"last_updated\"]\n"
"today\n"
"\n"
">>> product[\"lala\"] = \"test\"  # setting unknown field\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"    ...\n"
"KeyError: 'Product does not support field: lala'"
msgstr ""
">>>> product[\"last_updated\"] = \"todayy\"\n"
">>>> product[\"last_updated\"]\n"
"今日\n"
"\n"
">> product[\"lala\"] = \"test\" # 设置未知字段\n"
"Traceback(最近一次调用):\n"
"    . 。\n"
"密钥错误：“产品不支持字段: lala”"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:326
msgid "Accessing all populated values"
msgstr "访问所有有人居住的值"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:328
msgid "To access all populated values, just use the typical :class:`dict` API:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:330
msgid ""
">>> product.keys()\n"
"['price', 'name']\n"
"\n"
">>> product.items()\n"
"[('price', 1000), ('name', 'Desktop PC')]"
msgstr ""
">>> product.keys()\n"
"['price', 'name']\n"
"\n"
">> > product.items()\n"
"[('price', 1000) ('name', 'desktop PC')]"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:342
msgid "Copying items"
msgstr "复制项目"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:344
msgid ""
"To copy an item, you must first decide whether you want a shallow copy or a "
"deep copy."
msgstr "要复制一个物品，您必须首先决定是要一个浅色的副本还是深深的副本。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:347
msgid ""
"If your item contains :term:`mutable` values like lists or dictionaries, a "
"shallow copy will keep references to the same mutable values across all "
"different copies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:351
msgid ""
"For example, if you have an item with a list of tags, and you create a "
"shallow copy of that item, both the original item and the copy have the same "
"list of tags. Adding a tag to the list of one of the items will add the tag "
"to the other item as well."
msgstr ""
"例如，如果你有一个带有标签列表的项目，并且你创建了一个浅色的项目副本。 原始项"
"目和副本都有相同的标签列表。 将标签添加到其中一个项目的列表中，也会将标签添加"
"到其他项目中。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:356
msgid "If that is not the desired behavior, use a deep copy instead."
msgstr "如果这不是需要的行为，则使用深文本代替。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:358
msgid "See :mod:`copy` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:360
msgid ""
"To create a shallow copy of an item, you can either call :meth:`~scrapy.Item."
"copy` on an existing item (``product2 = product.copy()``) or instantiate "
"your item class from an existing item (``product2 = Product(product)``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:365
msgid ""
"To create a deep copy, call :meth:`~scrapy.Item.deepcopy` instead "
"(``product2 = product.deepcopy()``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:370
msgid "Other common tasks"
msgstr "其他共同任务"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:372
msgid "Creating dicts from items:"
msgstr "从项目创建口令："

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:374
msgid ""
">>> dict(product)  # create a dict from all populated values\n"
"{'price': 1000, 'name': 'Desktop PC'}\n"
"\n"
"Creating items from dicts:\n"
"\n"
">>> Product({\"name\": \"Laptop PC\", \"price\": 1500})\n"
"Product(price=1500, name='Laptop PC')\n"
"\n"
">>> Product({\"name\": \"Laptop PC\", \"lala\": 1500})  # warning: unknown "
"field in dict\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"    ...\n"
"KeyError: 'Product does not support field: lala'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:391
msgid "Extending Item subclasses"
msgstr "扩展项目子类"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:393
msgid ""
"You can extend Items (to add more fields or to change some metadata for some "
"fields) by declaring a subclass of your original Item."
msgstr ""
"您可以通过声明原始项目的亚类来扩展项目 (添加更多字段或更改某些字段的元数据)。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:396
msgid "For example:"
msgstr "例如："

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:398
msgid ""
"class DiscountedProduct(Product):\n"
"    discount_percent = scrapy.Field(serializer=str)\n"
"    discount_expiration_date = scrapy.Field()"
msgstr ""
"类折扣 Product(Product):\n"
"    discount_per = scrapy.Field(serializer=str)\n"
"    discount_expiration_date = scrapy.Field()"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:404
msgid ""
"You can also extend field metadata by using the previous field metadata and "
"appending more values, or changing existing values, like this:"
msgstr ""
"您也可以通过使用先前的字段元数据和附加更多的值或更改现有的值来扩展字段元数"
"据，如："

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:407
msgid ""
"class SpecificProduct(Product):\n"
"    name = scrapy.Field(Product.fields[\"name\"], serializer=my_serializer)"
msgstr ""
"class SpecificProduct(Product):\n"
"    name = scrapy.Field(Product.fields[\"name\"], serializer=my_serializer)"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:412
msgid ""
"That adds (or replaces) the ``serializer`` metadata key for the ``name`` "
"field, keeping all the previously existing metadata values."
msgstr ""
"添加(或替换) ``name`` 字段的 ``serializer`` 元数据键，保留所有以前存在的元数"
"据值。"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:421
msgid "Supporting All Item Types"
msgstr "支持所有项目类型"

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:423
msgid ""
"In code that receives an item, such as methods of :ref:`item pipelines "
"<topics-item-pipeline>` or :ref:`spider middlewares <topics-spider-"
"middleware>`, it is a good practice to use the :class:`~itemadapter."
"ItemAdapter` class to write code that works for any supported item type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/items.rst:430
msgid "Other classes related to items"
msgstr "与项目相关的其他类"

#: ../../../../scrapy/item.py:docstring of scrapy.item.ItemMeta:1
msgid "Metaclass_ of :class:`Item` that handles field definitions."
msgstr ""
